
- Compilation:
  make all

- Execution :
  ./skybkg_angelica_range
  
  Answer a couple of questions, for example to generate model at 150 and 160 MHz :
   Input frequency range at which to make a map [in MHz]
   Lower limit :
   150
   Upper limit :
   160
   Enter the step [in MHz] :
   10
   Base file name of file in which to save the map ?
   gsm           
   Enter name of output directory [default = skymaps/]
   gsm

- .dat.gz files required to generate model files are available at :
     https://www.dropbox.com/sh/xt6qxlyhxrskw1k/AACH5rneuATCQS2MTZFhHyn9a?dl=0

   tar zxvf data.tar.gz    
   


- Output files will be in subdirectory gsm/ in two files :
  gsm_ni150.00.out 
  gsm_ni160.00.out
  
  They are healpix ordered brightness temperature acroess the entire sky and can be used as an input to showspec program 



- .out files generated every 10 MHz are available at :
    https://www.dropbox.com/sh/xt6qxlyhxrskw1k/AACH5rneuATCQS2MTZFhHyn9a?dl=0
   tar zxvf gsm.tar.gz    


- Please reference the following paper :

http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2008MNRAS.388..247D

